## Backend

# PostgreSQL Database
POSTGRES_HOST=localhost
POSTGRES_PORT=5432
POSTGRES_DB=mindscribe
POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your_secure_postgres_password

# Server
PORT=8000
BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8000
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Auth
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=super-secret

# LLM Configuration
LLM_MODEL=gpt-3.5-turbo
LLM_EMBEDDING_MODEL=text-embedding-004
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key

# Google OAuth
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret

# GitHub OAuth
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_client_id
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_client_secret

## Frontend

# API
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Google OAuth
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id

# GitHub OAuth
VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_client_id

## Setting up OAuth Credentials

### Google OAuth

1. Visit [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2. Create a new project or select an existing one
3. Go to "APIs & Services" → "Credentials"
4. Click "Create Credentials" → "OAuth client ID"
5. Select "Web application"
6. Add authorized redirect URIs:
   - `http://localhost:5173`
   - `http://localhost:5173/auth/google/callback` (not required for implicit flow)
   - Your production domain
7. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret

### GitHub OAuth

1. Go to GitHub Settings → Developer settings → [OAuth Apps](https://github.com/settings/developers)
2. Click "New OAuth App"
3. Fill in the application details:
   - **Application name**: MindScribe
   - **Homepage URL**: `http://localhost:5173`
   - **Authorization callback URL**: `http://localhost:5173/auth/github/callback`
4. Copy the Client ID and generate a Client Secret
5. Update for production with your domain
